<% include ../partials/header-java.ejs %>

<!-- Turorial steps -->
<div class="container">

  <p class="mt-3">In this section, you will install the necessary tools, runtimes and SDKs to create <a href="https://java.com" target="_blank">Java</a> apps on your Mac.</p>
  
  <!-- Step 1 -->
  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="card-header text-white" style="background-color: #00AA9E;">Step 1.1: Install Homebrew and Java</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-3">Skip this step if you already have Brew and Java installed on your Mac.</h6>
        <p class="card-text">Run the command below in a Terminal window to install <a href="https://brew.sh" target="_blank">Homebrew.</a></p>

        <pre class="command-line" data-user="sanjay" data-host="MacBook">
          <code class="language-bash">
            ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"
          </code>
        </pre>

        <p class="card-text">Close the Terminal window you opened earlier and open a new one. Run the command below in the Terminal window to install the latest Java Runtime and the Java SDK.</p>

        <pre class="command-line" data-user="sanjay" data-host="MacBook">
          <code class="language-bash">
            brew update
            brew cask install java
          </code>
        </pre>

        <p class="card-text">Run the command below in the Terminal window to verify that the Java Runtime and SDK are installed properly.</p>

        <pre class="command-line" data-user="sanjay" data-host="MacBook">
          <code class="language-bash">
            javac --version
          </code>
        </pre>
                
        <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-star text-success"></span>&nbsp;You have sucessfully installed Homebrew and Java on your Mac!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Step 2 -->
  <div class="card mt-3">
    <div class="card-block">
      <div class="card-header text-white" style="background-color: #00AA9E;">Step 1.2: Install Maven</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <h6 class="card-subtitle mb-3">Skip this step if you already have Maven installed on your Mac.</h6>
        <p class="card-text">We'll use <a href="https://maven.apache.org" target="_blank">Apache Maven</a> to help manage dependencies, build, test and run Java projects. Run the command below in a Terminal window to install Maven.</p>

        <pre class="command-line" data-user="sanjay" data-host="MacBook">
          <code class="language-bash">
            brew install maven
          </code>
        </pre>

        <p class="card-text">Run the command below in the Terminal window to verify that the Maven is installed properly.</p>

        <pre class="command-line" data-user="sanjay" data-host="MacBook">
          <code class="language-bash">
            mvn -v
          </code>
        </pre>
        
          <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-star text-success"></span>&nbsp;You have successfully installed Java and Maven.</p>

          <p class="card-text"><span class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up text-success"></span>&nbsp;You have everything you need to create Java apps on your Mac!</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container text-center">
  <a class="btn btn-primary btn-md m-4 button-fixed-width-300 active" style="text-align:center" href="/sdk/java2">Go to step 2</a>
</div>

